Alcaraz will next face Frenchman Arthur Rinderknech, who is into the fourth round of a major for the first time aged 30. The No. 2 player in the PIF ATP Rankings leads their Lexus ATP Head2Head series 3-0, including a victory at the 2021 US Open and another earlier this year at Queen's Club.

“He's really difficult to play against, really aggressive, big serve, trying to go to the net, so it's going to be really difficult,” Alcaraz said. “But as I said, I'm just trying to be focused on myself, that I'm playing great tennis, and I'm feeling really comfortable physically, mentally, and just feeling the ball really well.

“I will try to think just about my goals, about myself, and let's see, but it's going to be a really interesting one.”



